snippet.textDisplay: I know what the first driver felt like.  I gave a coworker a ride to work, only to find the cops were waiting on him when we got to work.  I had multiple guns pointed at me, wound up in handcuffs for over 30 minutes.  He tried to dump a shitload of cocaine in my car and run....but he only made it a few feet before the cop threatened to shoot him.  Long story short, I was respectful and honest with the cops and they believed me and let me go on to work.  The other guy is still in prison a year later.  I don’t give anybody a ride anymore unless I really know them well.  It nearly ruined my life.
